extends ../layout

block vars
  - const path = 'en/';
  - const events = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('src/en/events.json'));

block description
  p SIGPX is a Japanese domestic study group for those interested in programming environments and their programming experience, founded in January 2016. We gather for exchanging information on state-of-the-art research and development projects relevant to programming experience.

block body
  section#overview
    p.detail
      strong Why now? What is this all about?
      |  ── When all computer users were programmers before the birth of Graphical User Interface and the 
      abbr(title='Window, Icon, Menu, Pointer') WIMP
      |  metaphor, there used to be no distinguishment between research on Programming Language, Software Engineering, Human-Computer Interaction, and User Interface. Later on, there came to be a gulf between "the programmer" and "the end user," resulting in the division of research domains. Now is the time when people say anybody {can, should} learn how to do programming ── so, 
      strong
        | why not think of 
        abbr(title='programming experience') PX
        |  (cf. 
        abbr(title='user experience') UX
        | ) from an interdisciplinary perspective?
      |  It seems to be a good timing for all of us to gather interdisciplinary knowledge of relevant research domains.
    p.detail
      | Companies often develop and deploy the state-of-the-art technologies in the field of informatics. It does not make sense to divide research and development. Those who do crazy things are ubiquitous among companies, universities, and research laboratories. We should gather regardless of our affiliations and positions, such as researchers and engineers, 
      strong to discuss programming experience ── to shape the future of programming.
    p.detail
      strong Who are you?
      |  ── 
      strong Researchers
      |  in the relevant research domains such as Programming Language, Software Engineering, Human-Computer Interaction, and User Interface; 
      strong Software engineers
      |  authoring programming environments including Programming Language, Software Development Tools, Integrated Development Environments; 
      strong Cognitive psychologists
      |  and 
      strong anybody interested in Programming Experience
      | .
  #events
  each event in events
    section(id=event.id)
      h2
        != event.title
        |  
        span.gray (#{event.date})
        if event.label
          != ' '
          span.label= event.label
      if event.details.length
        ul
          each detail in event.details
            li
              strong= detail.label
              != ' ' + detail.content
      if event.summary
        p!= event.summary
      p.details
        a(href=event.link) More Details? ☺
        br
  section#related-events
    h2 Relevant Events and Conferences
    dl
      dt
        a(href='https://liveprog.org/') LIVE: Workshop on Live Programming
      //
        
            <dd>2016年からは毎年開催となった。2013年の初回については下記参照。</dd>
        
      dt
        a(href='https://2021.plateau-workshop.org/') PLATEAU: Workshop on the Intersection of HCI and PL
        |  (previously: Workshop on Evaluation and Usability of Programming Languages and Tools)
      //
        
            <dd>Human-Computer Interaction分野が中心となって、プログラミング言語やツールの評価、ユーザビリティについて議論するワークショップを始めたもの。近年はPL・HCIの結節点という観点を重視。</dd>
        
      dt
        a(href='https://sites.google.com/site/vlhcc2016/') VL/HCC: IEEE Symposium on Visual Languages and Human-Centric Computing
      //
        
            <dd>ビジュアルプログラミング言語に関する国際シンポジウムだったものが、Human-Computer Interaction寄りのプログラミング研究を取り込んでできた国際会議。</dd>
        
      dt
        a(href='http://2015.splashcon.org/track/onward2015-papers') SPLASH Onward!
      //
        
            <dd>プログラミングに関する先進的な概念を発表するための国際ワークショップ。SPLASHのメイントラックであるOOPSLAほど evaluation を課さない代わりに &quot;grand visions and new paradigms&quot; を要求している。</dd>
        
      dt
        a(href='http://uist.acm.org/uist2015/about') UIST: Annual ACM Symposium on User Interface Software and Technology
      //
        
            <dd>ユーザインタフェースに関するトップ国際ワークショップ。プログラミング環境に関する研究もある。</dd>
        
      dt
        a(href='http://chi2016.acm.org/wp/') CHI: Annual ACM Conference on Human Factors in Computing Systems
      //
        
            <dd>Human-Computer Interactionに関するトップ国際会議。プログラミング環境に関する研究もときどきある。</dd>
        
      dt
        a(href='http://www.future-programming.org/') Future Programming Workshop
        |  (Co-located w/ 
        a(href='http://2015.splashcon.org/')
          abbr(title='The ACM SIGPLAN conference on Systems, Programming, Languages and Applications: Software for Humanity (SPLASH)') SPLASH
        |  2015)
      //
        
